[[哈利斯科州|哈利斯科州]]和[[纳亚里特州|纳亚里特州]]的降雨量在100到200毫米之间<ref>{{cite web |publisher=Comisión Nacional del Agua |author=Servicio Meteorológico Nacional Mexico |url=http://smn.cna.gob.mx/boletin/avisos/atlantico/atlantico.html |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5RN9OAnZN?url=http://smn.cna.gob.mx/boletin/avisos/atlantico/atlantico.html |archivedate=2007-08-26 |deadurl=yes |title=Remanentes del Ciclón Tropical "Dean" |date=2007-08-03 |accessdate=2007-08-26 }}</ref>，哈利斯科因此爆发[[泥石流|泥石流]]，有十套房屋受到影响，其中的一位住户因此遇难<ref name="earthtimes_mex_impact">{{cite news | author = Staff Writer | agency = earthtimes.org | date = 2007-08-24 | accessdate = 2007-08-24 | title = Death toll reaches 11 from Hurricane Dean in Mexico}}</ref>。[[普埃布拉州|普埃布拉州]]有五人因山崩丧生，还有一位居民因家中的围墙倒塌而被压死。韦拉克鲁斯州有一人在修补屋顶时因接触到[[输電系统|电线]]导致[[触电|触电]]身亡，[[米却肯州|米却肯州]]有一人在树下被风暴外围雨带产生的[[闪电|闪电]]击中而死，伊达尔戈州还有两人因屋顶塌落遇难<ref name="telegraph_mex_2007-08-24" /><ref name="wap_mex_impact">{{cite web |author=Tomas Bravo |publisher=Reuters |date=2007-08-22 |accessdate=2007-08-22 |title=Hurricane Dean slams Mexico's Gulf coast, kills two |deadurl=yes |url=http://mobile.alertnet.org/thenews/newsdesk/N22182914.htm |archivedate=2008-09-20 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5axkv2CYT?url=http://www.alertnet.org/thenews/newsdesk/N22182914.htm }}</ref>。整个墨西哥共有12人因飓风迪安丧生，但其中没有任何一位是在其首次在尤卡坦半岛登陆的高强度时期遇难<ref name="TCR" />。两次登陆造成的损失中农业占绝大部分，共计达到1.6亿美元<ref name="MEX_DMG_TOTAL">{{cite news | author = Staff Writer | agency = Agrointernet | date = 2007-09-11 | accessdate = 2008-09-12 | title = Mas de 2 mil millones de pesos los daños por dean en Quinta Roo}}</ref>。

{{Most intense Atlantic hurricanes}}

=== 伯利兹 ===
伯利兹北部边境的[[科罗萨尔镇|科罗萨尔镇]]是该国受影响最严重的地区，到处都是倒塌的树木<ref name="NPR_Belize_21-08-2007" />，还有报道称发生轻度洪灾<ref name="USDef_2007-08-22">{{cite web | author = Tech. Sgt. Sonny Cohrs | publisher = American Forces Press Service, News Articles | date = 2007-08-22 | accessdate = 2008-07-23 | title = U.S. Assessment Team Arrives in Belize Behind Hurricane Dean | archivedate = 2014-01-15 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140115061136/http://www.defense.gov/News/NewsArticle.aspx?ID=47139 | deadurl = no | url = http://www.defense.gov/news/newsarticle.aspx?id=47139}}</ref>。有八千人进入避难所躲避，不过他们都在不到两天内相继返回家园<ref name="ReliefWeb_SitRep6" />。伯利兹卫生部报道全国没有出现人员丧生，只有为数不多的几人出现轻伤<ref name="ReliefWeb_SitRep6">{{cite web | author = United Nations Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs (OCHA) | publisher = ReliefWeb | date = 2007-08-22 | accessdate = 2014-03-13 | title = Hurricane Dean OCHA Situation Report No. 6 | url = http://reliefweb.int/report/mexico/hurricane-dean-ocha-situation-report-no-6 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140313095930/http://reliefweb.int/report/mexico/hurricane-dean-ocha-situation-report-no-6 | archivedate = 2014-03-13 | deadurl = no}}</ref>。

伯利兹的农业受到严重损失，甘蔗田和[[木瓜|木瓜]]作物受到大面积破坏<ref name="USDef_2007-08-22" /><ref name="Blake_Hounshell">{{cite web | author = Blake Hounshell | publisher = Foreign Policy | date = 2007-08-22 | accessdate = 2008-07-24 | title = Hurricane Dean's big winner: sugar? | archivedate = 2014-01-03 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140103005703/http://blog.foreignpolicy.com/posts/2007/08/22/hurricane_deans_big_winner_sugar#sthash.kS3V23O5.dpbs | url = http://blog.foreignpolicy.com/posts/2007/08/22/hurricane_deans_big_winner_sugar}}</ref>。伯利兹政府的国家应急管理机构估计迪安给该国的木瓜产业造成3000万[[贝里斯元|贝里斯元]]的损失，失去的24平方公里甘蔗也导致制糖业遭受360万贝里斯元的损失<ref name="SanPedroSun_2007-08-30">{{cite web | author = Staff Writer | publisher = The San Pedro Sun | date = 2007-08-30 | accessdate = 2008-07-23 | title = Hurricane Dean costs Belize $107 Million + | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140102232219/http://www.sanpedrosun.com/old/07-342.html | deadurl = no | url = http://www.sanpedrosun.com/old/07-342.html | archivedate = 2014-01-02}}</ref>。伯利兹制糖工业公司报告该国的糖料作物数量和品质都是有纪录以来最差的一次，一共只生产44.5万公斤低于标准的甘蔗，而之前一年则生产有54.5万公斤的高质量甘蔗<ref name="LoveFM">{{cite web | author = Manuela Ayuso | publisher = LoveFM | date = 2008-07-08 | accessdate = 2011-09-30 | title = Worse sugar season reported by Belize sugar industry | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110930032829/http://www.lovefm.com/ndisplay.php?nid=8206 | archivedate = 2011-09-30 | url = http://www.lovefm.com/ndisplay.php?nid=8206}}</ref>。木瓜和甘蔗种植园遭受的破坏还致使上千人[[失业|失业]]<ref name="ReliefWeb_SitRep6" />。政府试图通过向受到迪安影响的[[农民|农民]]提供[[化肥|化肥]]来提高2008年糖类作物的收成，弥补这场风暴造成的损失<ref name="Gov_Belz_Cane_Fert">{{cite press release | author = Staff Writer | agency = Government of Belize, Ministry of Agriculture and Fisheries | date = 2008-01-14 | accessdate = 2008-07-24 | title = Northern Cane Farmers Provided with Much Needed Fertilizers}}</ref>。该国总理赛义德·穆萨估计飓风迪安一共给该国造成了1000万美元的损失<ref name="SanPedroSun_2007-08-30" />。

=== 其他地区 ===
[[尼加拉瓜|尼加拉瓜]]的[[卡克拉河|卡克拉河]]河口有一艘船在强风和大浪中沉没，船上一位年仅四岁的小女孩因此遇难，除此以外该国没有受到什么影响<ref name="Panta_2007-08-20_Nica01" />。

虽然飓风本身从未接近过[[美国本土|美国本土]]，但[[佛罗里达州|佛罗里达州]]的多个海滩还是报告出现大[[海浪|浪]]和[[回旋流|回旋流]]。迪安给[[西耶斯塔岛|西耶斯塔岛]]带去的乱流导致一人淹死，另外还有35人得到救援后脱险<ref name="TBO_usa_impact">{{cite web | author = Sarasota Herald-Tribune | publisher = The Tampa Tribune | date = 2007-08-23 | accessdate = 2014-03-13 | title = Lifeguards Rescue More Than 35 Off Siesta Key | archivedate = 2012-10-08 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121008055416/http://www2.tbo.com/news/breaking-news/2007/aug/23/lifeguards-rescue-more-35-currents-siesta-key-ar-167663/ | url = http://tbo.com/content/2007/aug/23/lifeguards-rescue-more-35-currents-siesta-key/news-breaking/}}</ref>。大浪还导致[[阿拉巴马州|阿拉巴马州]]的[[多芬岛_(阿拉巴马州)|多芬岛]]出现轻度洪灾，并造成约10万美元的损失<ref name="NCDCAlabamaseas">{{cite report | publisher = National Climatic Data Center | year = 2009 | accessdate = 2009-02-08 | title = NCDC Event Report: Alabama High Surf}}</ref>。迪恩的残留在太平洋徘徊数日后于8月26日早上从[[加利福尼亚州|加利福尼亚州]]的[[圣巴巴拉_(加利福尼亚州)|圣巴巴拉]]进入内地，带去强烈的雷暴，还在[[南加州|南加州]]沿海地区引发局部洪灾<ref name="San_Diego_Union_Tribune_S_California_impact">"{{cite web | author = SignOnSanDiego News Services | publisher = San Diego Union-Tribune | date = 2007-08-26 | accessdate = 2007-09-06 | title = Thunderstorms dump rain on North County | url = http://legacy.utsandiego.com/news/northcounty/20070826-0925-rain.html | archivedate = 2012-10-21 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121021122739/http://legacy.utsandiego.com/news/northcounty/20070826-0925-rain.html }}</ref>。残留部分于8月27日晨穿过[[莫哈韦沙漠|莫哈韦沙漠]]，[[拉斯维加斯|拉斯维加斯]]的日降雨量达到15毫米，创下新的纪录，也由此引发了山洪爆发和轻度破坏<ref name="AccuWeather_USA_SW_impact">"{{cite news | author = AccuWeather | publisher = AccuWeather | date = 2007-08-28 | accessdate = 2007-09-06 | title = AccuWeather — Weather News}}</ref>。

== 善后 ==
[[File:Freedom_of_the_seas.jpg|thumb]]的“[[海洋自由号|海洋自由号]]”是飓风迪安过去后第一艘造访牙买加的[[游船|游船]]，于8月22日停靠在[[奥乔里奥斯|奥乔里奥斯]]。]]

虽然迪安引起可观的破坏，但并没有对基础设施造成严重影响，大部分受影响的国家除农业领域外都迅速得以恢复。大部分邮轮公司都将船只改道远离加勒比西部，避开飓风的路线，但到了8月27日，除因受损而停靠在伯利兹和尤卡坦半岛的以外，其他所有游船都恢复原有航线。小安的列斯群岛和大安的列斯群岛的港口在数天内就恢复开放，所以邮轮服务也恢复得特别快。<ref name="Fodors" />

=== 小安的列斯群岛 ===
虽然迪安的北侧风眼墙经过马提尼克时，风暴的强度只达到二级飓风标准，但其产生的狂风和大面积洪灾仍然摧毁岛上70%的甘蔗作物和所有的香蕉作物，总计价值达4亿欧元<ref name="TCR" />，占该国年度国内生产总值的10%<ref name="Martinique_GDP">{{cite web|url=http://www.indexmundi.com/martinique/gdp_(purchasing_power_parity).html |title=Martinique GDP (purchasing power parity) |date=2006-11-01 |accessdate=2014-03-13 |publisher=IndexMundi |author=Staff Writer |archivedate=2012-09-22 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120922023734/http://www.indexmundi.com/martinique/gdp_%28purchasing_power_parity%29.html }}</ref>。不过该国的旅游业情况要好得多，只有少数几间酒店报告遭受轻度破坏，机场于飓风过去次日就恢复开放<ref name="Fodors" /><ref name="MARTINIQUE_For_Imd_release">{{cite web | author = Christel Coïta | publisher = For Immediate Release | date = 2007-08-21 | accessdate = 2014-03-13 | title = Martinique Tourism Industry Withstands Hurricane Dean | url = http://www.forimmediaterelease.net/pm/521.html | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140313170152/http://www.forimmediaterelease.net/pm/521.html | archivedate = 2014-03-13 }}</ref><ref name="Martinique_Govt_com">{{cite web|author=Steve Bennett |publisher=Martinique Promotion Bureau |date=2007-09-20 |accessdate=2008-07-24 |title=Hotels report minor cosmetic damage; airport re-opened Saturday, August 18 |url=http://www.martinique.org/contacts/press.htm |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090203113306/http://martinique.org/contacts/press.htm |archivedate=2009-02-03 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。除了在环境上仍不如以前外，岛上所有的酒店到8月底时都已全面恢复运营<ref name="Fodors" />。

[[法国海外部|法国海外部]]部长克里斯蒂安·艾斯特罗兹（{{lang|en|Christian Estrozy}}）和[[法国总理|总理]][[弗朗索瓦·菲永|弗朗索瓦·菲永]]前往法属加勒比岛屿评估风暴的破坏。他们估计风暴导致600人流离失所。他们简短的来访促使包括[[爱德华·格里桑特|爱德华·格里桑特]]（{{lang|en|Edouard Glissant}}）、[[帕特里克·查莫休|帕特里克·查莫休]]（{{lang|en|Patrick Chamoiseau}}）和[[拉斐尔·康菲恩特|拉斐尔·康菲恩特]]（{{lang|en|Raphael Confiant}}）在内的多位马提尼克[[作家|作家]]联名撰写[[公开信|公开信]]，表达各自对法国政坛以及如何处理飓风迪安善后事宜的关切。<ref name="caribnews_guad_aug_23">{{cite web|url=http://www.caribbeannetnews.com/guadeloupe/guadeloupe.php?news_id=3166&start=0&category_id=33 |title=Guadeloupe and Martinique after Dean |accessdate=2008-06-29 |date=2007-08-23 |publisher=Caribbean Net News |author=Danik Ibraheem Zandwonis |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090206023655/http://www.caribbeannetnews.com/guadeloupe/guadeloupe.php?news_id=3166&start=0&category_id=33 |archivedate=2009-02-06 }}</ref>

弗朗索瓦·菲永接下来带领一队来自[[法国内政部|法国内政部]]的专家前往瓜德罗普岛，评估破坏的程度和数额<ref name="caribnews_guad_aug_21">{{cite web|url=http://www.caribbeannetnews.com/guadeloupe/guadeloupe.php?news_id=3139&start=0&category_id=33 |title=French PM to visit hurricane-hit Caribbean islands |accessdate=2008-06-29 |date=2009-02-06 |publisher=Caribbean Net News |author=AP |deadurl=yes |archivedate=2009-02-06 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090206022017/http://www.caribbeannetnews.com/guadeloupe/guadeloupe.php?news_id=3139&start=0&category_id=33 }}</ref>。当地政府向他们报告瓜德罗普75%的香蕉种植园被彻底摧毁，价值达到1亿欧元<ref name="TCR" />。海外部部长克里斯蒂安·艾斯特罗兹承诺，所有的问题都会在三个月内解决<ref name="caribnews_guad_aug_30">{{cite web|url=http://www.caribbeannetnews.com/guadeloupe/guadeloupe.php?news_id=3302&start=0&category_id=33 |title=Dean caused 500m euro damage in French Caribbean |accessdate=2009-02-06 |date=2007-08-30 |publisher=Caribbean Net News |author=AP |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090206022022/http://www.caribbeannetnews.com/guadeloupe/guadeloupe.php?news_id=3302&start=0&category_id=33 |archivedate=2009-02-06 }}</ref>，但实际上香蕉的种植要一直到超过6个月后才重新启动，再又过了几个月才恢复失去的产能<ref name="caribnews_guad_aug_18">{{cite web|url=http://www.caribbeannetnews.com/guadeloupe/guadeloupe.php?news_id=3093&start=0&category_id=33 |title=Hurricane destroys Guadeloupe, Martinique bananas |accessdate=2009-02-06 |date=2007-08-18 |publisher=Caribbean Net News |author=AP |deadurl=yes |archivedate=2009-02-06 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090206024326/http://www.caribbeannetnews.com/guadeloupe/guadeloupe.php?news_id=3093&start=0&category_id=33 }}</ref>。除农业损失外，该岛只遭受轻微的风害和洪灾，这些都很快就得以修复<ref name="UN_News_Aug_21">{{cite web|url=http://www.un.org/apps/news/story.asp?NewsID=23562&Cr=hurricane&Cr1= |title=UN teams assessing aftermath in Caribbean nations hit by Hurricane Dean |accessdate=2014-03-13 |date=2007-08-21 |publisher=UN News Center |author=UN News Service |archivedate=2012-11-02 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121102185229/http://www.un.org/apps/news/story.asp?NewsID=23562&Cr=hurricane&Cr1= }}</ref>。

=== 牙买加 ===
[[File:1261116988_d1ee7382cb_o.jpg|thumb]][[诺曼·曼利国际机场|诺曼·曼利国际机场]]的道路在飓风迪安过后被[[沙子|沙子]]掩埋，需要动用重型机械来清除。]]

8月24日，[[牙买加总理|牙买加总理]][[波蒂亚·辛普森-米勒|波蒂亚·辛普森-米勒]]宣布政府将提供2.25亿[[牙买加元|牙买加元]]对该国农业产业提供紧急援助。这次援助主要是针对该国受灾最严重的教区<ref name="reliefweb_jam_ag_2007-08-24_01">{{cite web|author=Government of Jamaica |publisher=Relief Web |date=2007-08-24 |accessdate=2007-08-26 |title=Jamaica: $225 million in emergency aid for agricultural sector |archivedate=2014-03-13 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140313141828/http://reliefweb.int/report/jamaica/jamaica-225-million-emergency-aid-agricultural-sector |url=http://reliefweb.int/report/jamaica/jamaica-225-million-emergency-aid-agricultural-sector }}</ref>。她还宣布向紧急住房维修提供5亿牙买加元的补助和低息贷款，还向屋顶需要修补的居民提供油布供其暂时度过难关，且不收取任何费用<ref name="reliefweb_jam_house_2007-08-24">{{cite web|author=Government of Jamaica |publisher=Relief Web |date=2007-08-24 |accessdate=2007-08-26 |title=Jamaica: NHT establishes $500 million loan fund for emergency repairs |url=http://reliefweb.int/report/jamaica/jamaica-nht-establishes-500-million-loan-fund-emergency-repairs |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140313142215/http://reliefweb.int/report/jamaica/jamaica-nht-establishes-500-million-loan-fund-emergency-repairs |archivedate=2014-03-13 |deadurl=no }}</ref>。

世界粮食计划署立即开始向5500名牙买加人提供补充性的粮食援助，每天的口粮为1900[[焦耳|千焦]]（450[[卡路里|千卡]]）能量的[[高能量饼干|高能量饼干]]，并持续发放两个[[星期|星期]]<ref name="WFP_aug_30">{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090817112831/http://www.alertnet.org/thenews/newsdesk/WFP/273c26b985877efbe3edcfa7a95dc2fd.htm |url=http://www.alertnet.org/thenews/newsdesk/WFP/273c26b985877efbe3edcfa7a95dc2fd.htm |title=Hurricane Dean aftermath: WFP assisting over 10,000 victims in Jamaica and Belize |accessdate=2009-08-17 |date=2007-08-30 |publisher=Reuters |author=World Food Program |deadurl=yes |archivedate=2009-08-17 }}</ref>。在三天的时间里，[[美国国际开发署|美国国际开发署]]预先准备好的价值39.8万美元紧急求援物资就送到岛上。大部分床垫，毛毯，塑料布，卫生用品和水容器都由空运送来<ref name="reliefweb_jam_USAID_2007-08-24" />。[[美洲开发银行|美洲开发银行]]提供20万美元赠款支援救灾工作<ref name="reliefweb_jam_IDB_2007-08-24">{{cite web|author=Inter-American Development Bank (IDB) |publisher=Relief Web |date=2007-08-24 |accessdate=2007-08-26 |title=IDB approves US$200,000 grant for relief efforts in Jamaica |url=http://reliefweb.int/report/jamaica/idb-approves-us200000-grant-relief-efforts-jamaica |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140313143330/http://reliefweb.int/report/jamaica/idb-approves-us200000-grant-relief-efforts-jamaica |archivedate=2014-03-13 |deadurl=no }}</ref>，正在处理[[台风圣帕_(2007年)|圣风圣帕]]救灾工作的[[中华人民共和国|中华人民共和国]]红十字会也向牙买加送去3万美元用于购买紧急救灾物资<ref name="reliefweb_jam_redcross_2007-08-25">{{cite web|author=Government of Jamaica |publisher=Relief Web |date=2007-08-25 |accessdate=2007-08-26 |title=Jamaica: Chinese Red Cross donates US$30,000 for hurricane relief |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140313143614/http://reliefweb.int/report/jamaica/jamaica-chinese-red-cross-donates-us30000-hurricane-relief |url=http://reliefweb.int/report/jamaica/jamaica-chinese-red-cross-donates-us30000-hurricane-relief |archivedate=2014-03-13 |deadurl=no }}</ref>。

飓风袭击该岛四个月后，[[世界银行|世界银行]]董事会于2007年12月批准1000万美元的紧急贷款<ref name="Relief_Web_Jam_Dec_20">{{cite web|archivedate=2014-03-13 |deadurl=no |title=World Bank approves US$10 million to restore basic community infrastructure in the aftermath of Hurricane Dean |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140313143843/http://reliefweb.int/report/jamaica/world-bank-approves-us10-million-restore-basic-community-infrastructure-aftermath |url=http://reliefweb.int/report/jamaica/world-bank-approves-us10-million-restore-basic-community-infrastructure-aftermath |accessdate=2014-03-13 |date=2007-12-20 |publisher=Relief Web |author=The World Bank Group }}</ref>。世界银行加勒比董事和牙买加财政部长通过谈判达成为期17年的还款方案，并将资金汇入牙买加飓风迪安紧急恢复项目。负责落实这一项目的牙买加社会投资基金会使用这笔资金“重建和支持受这场飓风影响的学校、医疗中心、社区和田间道路”<ref name="Relief_Web_Jam_Jan_8">{{cite web | archivedate = 2014-03-13 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140313144838/http://reliefweb.int/report/jamaica/jamaica-receives-us10-million-restore-basic-community-infrastructure-aftermath | accessdate = 2014-03-13 | date = 2008-01-08 | | author = The World Bank Group | url = http://reliefweb.int/report/jamaica/jamaica-receives-us10-million-restore-basic-community-infrastructure-aftermath | title = Jamaica receives US$10 million to restore basic community infrastructure in the aftermath of Hurricane Dean | publisher = Relief Web}}</ref><ref name="World_Bank_Jam_Loan">{{cite web | url = http://www.worldbank.org/projects/P109575/jamaica-hurricane-dean-erl?lang=en&tab=overview | title = Jamaica Hurricane Dean ERL | accessdate = 2014-03-13 | date = 2008-01-08 | publisher = The World Bank Group | author = The World Bank Group}}</ref>。飓风迪安紧急恢复项目最终在2008年6月拉开帷幕，其中农村公路维修合同数额达到3700万牙买加元<ref name="JIS_June)26">{{cite web | url = http://jis.gov.jm/hurricane-dean-recovery-project-to-be-launched-on-friday/ | title = Jamaica Hurricane Dean Recovery Project to be Launched on Friday | accessdate = 2014-03-13 | date = 2008-06-26 | publisher = Jamaica Information Service | author = Office of the Prime Minister | archive-date = 2016-03-17 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160317023952/http://jis.gov.jm/hurricane-dean-recovery-project-to-be-launched-on-friday/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

2008年夏末，牙买加的香蕉产量已经恢复到迪安来袭前的水平。在[[欧洲联盟|欧盟]]香蕉支援计划署提供的11亿牙买加元帮助下，数千英亩土地得以再植。香蕉片是该国在夏季开始时第一个准备[[出口贸易|出口]]的产品，之后不久就开始新鲜香蕉的生产。<ref name="Min_of_Ag_Jam_Bananas">{{cite web | author = Chris Patterson | publisher = Government of Jamaica, Ministry of Agriculture | date = 2008-06-25 | accessdate = 2014-03-13 | title = Banana Industry to be Fully Recovered by the End of Summer | url = http://jis.gov.jm/banana-industry-to-be-fully-recovered-by-the-end-of-summer/ | archive-date = 2014-03-13 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140313181005/http://jis.gov.jm/banana-industry-to-be-fully-recovered-by-the-end-of-summer/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>

=== 墨西哥 ===
[[File:Costa_maya_from_cruise_ship.jpg|right]]
虽然迪安在墨西哥登陆的地区相对来说人烟稀少，并且对其路径的准确预报也给予充分的警告，但这场风暴还是造成非常严重的破坏。距登陆点最近的玛哈瓦镇经受飓风最强风力的摧残，有数百幢建筑物被毁<ref name="TCR" />。金塔纳罗奥州州长费利克斯·冈萨雷斯·坎托（{{lang|es|Félix González Canto}}）表示，虽然州首府切图马尔的清理工作在三个星期内就已完成，但全州的更多农村道路花超过六个月时间才全部修复<ref name="Fodors" />。州政府也因无法处理好飓风的善后工作而向联邦政府申请援助。他们一起设立一个住房修复基金，向超过37000位居民的住房重建提供援助<ref name="Calderon_speech">{{cite web | author = Miguel Hidalgo | publisher = Relief Web | date = 2007-10-31 | accessdate = 2014-03-13 | title = México: El Presidente Calderón en la entrega de viviendas a damnificados por el Huracán Dean | archivedate = 2014-03-13 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140313151324/http://reliefweb.int/report/mexico/m%C3%A9xico-el-presidente-calder%C3%B3n-en-la-entrega-de-viviendas-damnificados-por-el-hurac%C3%A1n | url = http://reliefweb.int/report/mexico/m%C3%A9xico-el-presidente-calder%C3%B3n-en-la-entrega-de-viviendas-damnificados-por-el-hurac%C3%A1n}}</ref>。

科斯塔玛雅的邮轮洪口受到严重破坏，导致[[嘉年华邮轮|嘉年华邮轮]]和皇家加勒比国际游轮这两家全世界最大的游轮公司改变航线，直到2009年才开始恢复在此停靠<ref name="LATimes_Cruise">{{cite web | author = AP | publisher = Los Angeles Times | date = 2007-09-19 | accessdate = 2011-09-30 | title = Much Hurricane Dean damage at Mexico's Puerto Costa Maya | |deadurl = yes | archivedate = 2011-09-30 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110930155346/http://travel.latimes.com/articles/la-trw-hurricane-dean-damage-at-mexico-port19sep07?parent=tours-cruises&type=interests | url = http://travel.latimes.com/articles/la-trw-hurricane-dean-damage-at-mexico-port19sep07?parent=tours-cruises&type=interests}}</ref>。墨西哥政府迅速拨款重建被摧毁的混凝土码头<ref name="fund_piers">{{cite web | author = Maite Velez-Couto | publisher = Valente Travel Inc. | date = 2007-09-11 | accessdate = 2014-03-13 | title = Costa Maya begins rebuilding process | url = http://www.valentetravel.com/newsdetails.php?id=123 | archivedate = 2014-01-05 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140105195404/http://www.valentetravel.com/newsdetails.php?id=123}}</ref>，2008年6月，经过重建的码头可以容纳的船型已经比之前更大<ref name="NETCOT">{{cite web | author = Staff Writer | publisher = Caribbean News Digital | date = 2008-10-09 | accessdate = 2008-09-19 | title = Costa Maya Reopens with New Zip-Line Adventure | url = http://www.caribbeannewsdigital.com/en/noticia/costa-maya-reopens-new-zip-line-adventure | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140102193022/http://www.caribbeannewsdigital.com/en/noticia/costa-maya-reopens-new-zip-line-adventure | archivedate = 2014-01-02 | deadurl = yes }}</ref>。

包括联合国人员在内的大部分观察人士起初称赞墨西哥联邦政府面对这场风暴做出迅速而充分的准备，因此造成的死亡人数很少<ref name="scoop_aug_2007" /><ref name="UN_applauds" />。然而风暴过后，对于援助的分配却出现多项有关政治动机的指控。[[费利佩·卡尔德龙|费利佩·卡尔德龙]]领导的[[墨西哥国家行动党|墨西哥国家行动党]]成员分发的袋装[[面包|面包]]上标有该党的标识，但这些面包却是由国家的救灾库房资助的。韦拉克鲁斯州州长菲德尔·埃雷拉受到墨西哥国家行动党和自己所在的[[革命制度党|革命制度党]]指控，指责他动用包括救灾资金在内的州内资源资助革命制度党候选人的竞选<ref name="goliath_mex">{{cite web|author=SourceMex |publisher=Goliath Business Knowledge on Demand |date=2007-08-29 |accessdate=2014-03-13 |title=Hurricane Dean causes minimal damage in Mexico despite storm's high intensity |via=TheFreeLibrary |archivedate=2014-03-13 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140313154114/http://www.thefreelibrary.com/HURRICANE%2BDEAN%2BCAUSES%2BMINIMAL%2BDAMAGE%2BIN%2BMEXICO%2BDESPITE%2BSTORM%27S%2BHIGH...-a0168182376 |url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/HURRICANE+DEAN+CAUSES+MINIMAL+DAMAGE+IN+MEXICO+DESPITE+STORM'S+HIGH...-a0168182376 }}</ref>。

=== 退役 ===
飓风迪安是15年来第一个以五级强度登陆的风暴，由于造成大范围的破坏，[[世界气象组织|世界气象组织]]于2008年5月13日在[[奥兰多_(佛罗里达州)|奥兰多]]举行的年度会议上将其名称迪安退役，之后都不会再在大西洋风暴命名中使用。用来代替的新名称是多利安（{{lang|en|Dorian}}），这个名称于[[2013年大西洋飓风季|2013年大西洋飓风季]]中首度使用。<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.noaanews.noaa.gov/stories2008/20080513_stormnames.html | title = Dean, Felix and Noel "Retired" from List of Storm Names | accessdate = 2014-03-13 | date = 2008-05-13 | author = NOAA | publisher = NOAA | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130807135700/http://www.noaanews.noaa.gov/stories2008/20080513_stormnames.html | archivedate = 2013-08-07 | deadurl = no}}</ref><ref>{{cite report | author = Daniel P. Brown | title = Tropical Cyclone Report: Tropical Storm Dorian | url = http://www.nhc.noaa.gov/data/tcr/AL042013_Dorian.pdf | publisher = National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration | work = National Hurricane Center | date = 2013-10-17 | accessdate = 2014-03-13 | format = PDF | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131214201541/http://www.nhc.noaa.gov/data/tcr/AL042013_Dorian.pdf | location = Miami, Florida | archivedate = 2013-12-14 | deadurl = no}}</ref>

